The '''golden-crested myna''' ('''''Ampeliceps coronatus''''') is a species in the [[starling]] and [[myna]] [[Family (taxonomy)|family]], [[Sturnidae]]. It is found from north-eastern [[India]] through [[Indochina]] and has been introduced to the [[British Indian Ocean Territory]]. Its main habitat is [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]], but it is also found in heavily degraded former forest.<ref name="iucn status 12 November 2021" />
